1
00:00:00,040 --> 00:00:03,215
This series features fictional characters

2
00:00:03,215 --> 00:00:05,904
and content based on cases of depression.

3
00:00:05,904 --> 00:00:08,846
Real-life symptoms and behaviors

4
00:00:08,846 --> 00:00:11,800
may vary from person to person.

5
00:00:11,800 --> 00:00:16,148
For more info or psychiatric consultation,

6
00:00:16,148 --> 00:00:19,240
call your local area's mental health hotline.

7
00:00:19,240 --> 00:00:21,273
Those with depression or similar symptoms

8
00:00:21,273 --> 00:00:24,760
should watch with a close companion.

9
00:00:24,760 --> 00:00:26,904
[Previously]
Could you please be a little kinder to me?

10
00:00:26,904 --> 00:00:28,062
I can do it now!

11
00:00:28,062 --> 00:00:29,605
Yay!

12
00:00:29,605 --> 00:00:33,434
Both about the guitar
and about me being a teacher.

13
00:00:33,434 --> 00:00:35,890
I won't stop you from doing anything anymore.

14
00:00:35,890 --> 00:00:37,690
I promise.

15
00:00:39,046 --> 00:00:42,883
I'm so glad you and your mom made up.

16
00:00:42,883 --> 00:00:44,642
You seem totally different now.

17
00:00:44,642 --> 00:00:46,949
I guess that's life.

18
00:00:46,949 --> 00:00:49,223
There's so much more to learn.

19
00:00:50,840 --> 00:00:52,920
[Atsara & Little Lion]

20
00:00:58,547 --> 00:01:01,631
Since I've been able
to play the guitar again,

21
00:01:03,198 --> 00:01:05,245
I've been trying to remember

22
00:01:05,245 --> 00:01:09,678
and find the song
that can get him to fall asleep.

23
00:01:09,678 --> 00:01:12,033
And it seems that things are...

24
00:01:15,856 --> 00:01:17,724
getting better.

25
00:01:29,726 --> 00:01:31,615
As if!

26
00:01:31,615 --> 00:01:35,604
It's been two weeks,
but I still can't find that song.

27
00:01:35,604 --> 00:01:36,877
But what can I do?

28
00:01:36,877 --> 00:01:38,939
I just have to keep trying.

29
00:01:50,022 --> 00:01:51,839
You're really focused.

30
00:01:52,834 --> 00:01:56,774
I have to,
so I can finally get Sun to fall asleep.

31
00:01:56,774 --> 00:01:59,961
Why do you want Sun to fall asleep so badly?

32
00:01:59,961 --> 00:02:01,779
Because I'm tired of him.

33
00:02:01,779 --> 00:02:04,037
But he's a good kid.

34
00:02:05,069 --> 00:02:06,602
Look at this.

35
00:02:08,136 --> 00:02:11,772
He washed my cream shirt
with colored clothes.

36
00:02:11,772 --> 00:02:13,917
Now it's pink.

37
00:02:18,405 --> 00:02:21,741
I know he wants to help,

38
00:02:21,741 --> 00:02:25,829
but if he's only making things worse,
he might as well do nothing.

39
00:02:25,829 --> 00:02:27,449
It'd be better if he didn't help at all, right?

40
00:02:27,449 --> 00:02:29,249
Yeah.

41
00:02:38,880 --> 00:02:39,960
[Saturday - Sun]

42
00:02:42,525 --> 00:02:44,465
Oh, shit.

43
00:02:44,465 --> 00:02:46,004
Sun!

44
00:03:50,159 --> 00:03:51,936
Excuse me.

45
00:03:51,936 --> 00:03:54,112
May I do the sweeping myself?

46
00:03:54,112 --> 00:03:55,934
Please take a break.

47
00:03:57,758 --> 00:04:01,760
Come on, Teacher Jee!
When are we going to learn?

48
00:04:01,760 --> 00:04:04,360
[Talent Stage]
We'll have to sweep again anyway.

49
00:04:06,614 --> 00:04:07,733
Jee!

50
00:04:07,733 --> 00:04:10,903
Sodchuen! Has anyone seen Sun?

51
00:04:10,903 --> 00:04:12,655
He ran away from the condo this morning.

52
00:04:12,655 --> 00:04:15,935
Damn. He managed to sneak out of the condo?

53
00:04:15,935 --> 00:04:17,711
He's smart.

54
00:04:17,711 --> 00:04:20,599
Have you asked the motorbike taxis
in front of the condo?

55
00:04:20,599 --> 00:04:22,000
I have.

56
00:04:22,000 --> 00:04:24,230
They said they dropped him off
near the school.

57
00:04:25,251 --> 00:04:28,812
But I was the first to arrive this morning
and I didn't see him.

58
00:04:28,812 --> 00:04:33,233
I don't think
a kid that age can get very far.

59
00:04:34,023 --> 00:04:38,560
Do any of our students live near the school?

60
00:04:38,560 --> 00:04:41,542
Are all men this bad everywhere in the world?

61
00:04:41,542 --> 00:04:45,614
Exactly. Men really are terrible.

62
00:04:48,548 --> 00:04:52,029
Right? I shouldn't have trusted him.

63
00:04:55,809 --> 00:04:57,284
Teacher Pobmek is calling.

64
00:04:57,284 --> 00:04:59,566
Teacher Jee is calling me too.

65
00:04:59,566 --> 00:05:03,705
They're calling at the same time.
Are they having a moment?

66
00:05:03,705 --> 00:05:06,196
No, that's a ghost ship.

67
00:05:06,196 --> 00:05:07,879
Don't pick up.

68
00:05:07,879 --> 00:05:11,419
Otherwise, the teachers will find out
about Sun.

69
00:05:12,691 --> 00:05:14,221
The kids are not picking up.

70
00:05:14,221 --> 00:05:16,204
Is there anyone else we can rely on?

71
00:05:16,204 --> 00:05:17,342
Your mom!

72
00:05:17,342 --> 00:05:20,290
Your mom is the only person we can rely on.

73
00:05:20,290 --> 00:05:21,616
You're right.

74
00:05:22,543 --> 00:05:24,657
Should we start our secret mission now?

75
00:05:24,657 --> 00:05:29,356
But we can't let the adults know
that I'm going to see my mom!

76
00:05:29,356 --> 00:05:30,934
Should we go to the police?

77
00:05:30,934 --> 00:05:33,520
Huh? The police?

78
00:05:33,520 --> 00:05:35,803
But Sun's been missing
for less than 24 hours.

79
00:05:35,803 --> 00:05:37,399
Will the police even take the report?

80
00:05:37,399 --> 00:05:40,935
We can just tell them
Sun is only 7 years old.

81
00:05:40,935 --> 00:05:44,018
Look at his body.
Do you think the police will believe us?

82
00:05:45,381 --> 00:05:46,754
What should we do?

83
00:05:46,754 --> 00:05:48,478
We don't have to do anything.

84
00:05:48,478 --> 00:05:49,754
Look at this.

85
00:05:49,754 --> 00:05:55,805
Today, we're on a secret mission
to take Sun to his mom!

86
00:05:55,805 --> 00:05:57,808
Thank you, Papa,

87
00:05:57,808 --> 00:06:03,205
for showing us that good men still exist.

88
00:06:03,205 --> 00:06:04,312
- Uncle.
- Yes?

89
00:06:04,312 --> 00:06:06,611
Can you buy me some snacks?

90
00:06:06,611 --> 00:06:07,709
I want to take some to my mom.

91
00:06:07,709 --> 00:06:09,256
Of course.

92
00:06:10,558 --> 00:06:12,566
Hold on, Elsa.

93
00:06:12,566 --> 00:06:16,010
Isn't this mission supposed to be a secret?

94
00:06:16,010 --> 00:06:17,826
Oh, she's right.

95
00:06:17,826 --> 00:06:20,804
But don't forget to follow me.

96
00:06:20,804 --> 00:06:23,014
Bye-bye.

97
00:06:25,557 --> 00:06:27,733
So he's running off to Mommy Pranee's house.

98
00:06:28,639 --> 00:06:30,162
Then what are we waiting for? Let's go.

99
00:06:30,162 --> 00:06:31,589
We can't just go.

100
00:06:31,589 --> 00:06:33,022
I don't know where she lives.

101
00:06:33,022 --> 00:06:35,174
What? How come?

102
00:06:35,174 --> 00:06:37,563
- Are you really her son-in-law?
- Of course I am!

103
00:06:37,563 --> 00:06:39,945
Hey! Stop fighting!

104
00:06:39,945 --> 00:06:42,440
I can look it up in Solar's records.

105
00:06:42,440 --> 00:06:44,161
Let's go.

106
00:06:44,161 --> 00:06:46,656
- We can look it up later.
- Jee, come here!

107
00:06:52,166 --> 00:06:53,966
This is it.

108
00:06:57,759 --> 00:06:59,952
Are you sure this is the right place?

109
00:06:59,952 --> 00:07:04,596
It has to be. His records say it's here.

110
00:07:04,596 --> 00:07:06,413
I don't think it's wrong.

111
00:07:13,100 --> 00:07:20,546
Aunt!

112
00:07:21,871 --> 00:07:23,863
- Damn it.
- Hey!

113
00:07:23,863 --> 00:07:26,344
What is it with him and gates?

114
00:07:29,373 --> 00:07:32,480
Wait, Teacher Jee. Will I be able to get in?

115
00:07:32,480 --> 00:07:34,487
Gosh!

116
00:07:34,487 --> 00:07:36,287
Teacher Jee!

117
00:07:38,494 --> 00:07:39,953
Excuse me, Aunt.

118
00:07:41,120 --> 00:07:42,362
Aunt.

119
00:07:42,362 --> 00:07:45,154
Oh my god! You guys startled me!

120
00:07:45,154 --> 00:07:47,524
What brings you here?

121
00:07:48,240 --> 00:07:52,203
- Well...
- Didn't Solar come with you?

122
00:07:52,203 --> 00:07:54,794
Sun ran away from the condo this morning.

123
00:07:54,794 --> 00:07:56,825
I think he's coming here.

124
00:07:56,825 --> 00:07:58,188
Huh?

125
00:07:59,835 --> 00:08:01,713
He's coming here?

126
00:08:02,955 --> 00:08:04,824
Is something wrong?

127
00:08:17,136 --> 00:08:18,619
Sun!

128
00:08:24,888 --> 00:08:26,820
Sun.

129
00:08:26,820 --> 00:08:28,797
Hey!

130
00:08:28,797 --> 00:08:29,989
What are you going to scold me for now?

131
00:08:29,989 --> 00:08:32,012
Aren't you tired of me? Huh?

132
00:08:32,012 --> 00:08:34,413
If you're so tired of me, just leave me.

133
00:08:42,233 --> 00:08:44,033
Sun,

134
00:08:46,087 --> 00:08:48,095
I'm sorry...

135
00:08:50,101 --> 00:08:52,520
for what I said to you this morning.

136
00:08:54,796 --> 00:08:57,522
I really do want to take care of you.

137
00:09:06,624 --> 00:09:08,926
Aren't you tired of me anymore?

138
00:09:08,926 --> 00:09:10,726
No.

139
00:09:11,784 --> 00:09:12,944
So I can jump on the bed?

140
00:09:12,944 --> 00:09:14,235
Yes.

141
00:09:14,235 --> 00:09:17,227
- And I can leave my toys out after I play?
- No.

142
00:09:17,227 --> 00:09:18,664
Fine.

143
00:09:22,026 --> 00:09:26,463
You must've missed your mom so much
that you had to go this far.

144
00:09:26,463 --> 00:09:28,019
Exactly.

145
00:09:28,943 --> 00:09:31,826
Then let's go see your mom.

146
00:09:31,826 --> 00:09:33,769
Where are you going?

147
00:09:33,769 --> 00:09:37,228
Your mom's house.

148
00:09:37,228 --> 00:09:39,133
This is my mom's house.

149
00:09:41,135 --> 00:09:42,761
Huh?

150
00:09:51,226 --> 00:09:53,229
Oh, hi, Teacher Pranee.

151
00:09:54,383 --> 00:09:57,316
How have you been? Long time no see.

152
00:09:57,316 --> 00:09:58,887
I'm good.

153
00:09:58,887 --> 00:10:01,184
How are you, Sun?

154
00:10:01,184 --> 00:10:02,984
I'm good.

155
00:10:05,496 --> 00:10:08,988
Have you seen my mom?

156
00:10:08,988 --> 00:10:11,027
It looks like she's not home.

157
00:10:13,203 --> 00:10:14,563
Aunt.

158
00:10:16,005 --> 00:10:17,833
What's going on here?

159
00:10:40,597 --> 00:10:42,756
Aunt,

160
00:10:42,756 --> 00:10:47,417
have you been lying to us this whole time
that you're Solar's mom?

161
00:10:48,124 --> 00:10:51,028
I'm sorry
for not telling you the whole truth.

162
00:10:51,814 --> 00:10:54,457
We've been trying so hard
to help Solar recover,

163
00:10:54,457 --> 00:10:56,372
but you've been lying to us?

164
00:10:56,372 --> 00:10:58,639
I had my reasons.

165
00:10:59,825 --> 00:11:04,744
And everything I did
was for Solar's own good.

166
00:11:07,352 --> 00:11:14,539
So who exactly... is Sun?

167
00:11:32,925 --> 00:11:34,725
The truth is,

168
00:11:36,218 --> 00:11:38,751
I'm not Sun's real mother.

169
00:11:44,414 --> 00:11:47,092
When yellow is mixed with blue, it becomes...

170
00:11:47,092 --> 00:11:50,152
- Green!
- Nice.

171
00:11:50,152 --> 00:11:54,646
I was an art teacher
at this elementary school.

172
00:11:55,417 --> 00:11:58,902
Sun was one of my students.

173
00:11:58,902 --> 00:12:03,348
Back then, he wasn't cheerful like Solar.

174
00:12:03,348 --> 00:12:05,428
On the contrary...

175
00:12:08,596 --> 00:12:10,393
Hey, give me the bag!

176
00:12:10,393 --> 00:12:12,434
Give it!

177
00:12:17,346 --> 00:12:19,277
Sun!

178
00:12:19,277 --> 00:12:21,117
Not you again!

179
00:12:25,358 --> 00:12:30,837
Everyone called Sun a troubled child.

180
00:12:35,444 --> 00:12:39,259
You're pretty good, huh?

181
00:12:39,259 --> 00:12:43,134
Can you help me out?

182
00:12:46,784 --> 00:12:51,146
I've been assigned to decorate this wall.

183
00:12:51,146 --> 00:12:52,988
Will you help me?

184
00:12:53,831 --> 00:12:55,631
Like this.

185
00:12:56,331 --> 00:12:58,616
Look. This is what we have to do.

186
00:13:01,186 --> 00:13:02,324
So, do you think you can do it?

187
00:13:02,324 --> 00:13:04,565
- Sure.
- Here, try this one.

188
00:13:04,565 --> 00:13:05,993
Okay.

189
00:13:08,319 --> 00:13:10,106
- How's that?
- That's purple!

190
00:13:10,106 --> 00:13:12,349
Here. Try some more.

191
00:13:12,349 --> 00:13:13,650
Go all out.

192
00:13:13,650 --> 00:13:15,450
Yes!

193
00:13:17,119 --> 00:13:22,453
How does that feel? Fun, right?

194
00:13:23,477 --> 00:13:26,288
See? This is way more fun
than throwing bottles.

195
00:13:27,272 --> 00:13:29,224
Look, Sun.

196
00:13:29,224 --> 00:13:32,131
Next time you feel like throwing something,

197
00:13:32,131 --> 00:13:36,433
come throw paint balloons with me, okay?

198
00:13:37,301 --> 00:13:42,770
Is that okay?

199
00:13:42,770 --> 00:13:48,536
I was basically Sun's only friend then.

200
00:13:50,904 --> 00:13:55,784
And we weren't just friends.
We were neighbors too.

201
00:13:55,784 --> 00:13:57,626
Wait, Sun.

202
00:13:59,163 --> 00:14:01,341
I have something for you.

203
00:14:08,447 --> 00:14:12,385
From now on, if something's bothering you,

204
00:14:12,385 --> 00:14:16,125
you can use these crayons to color it out
in this book,

205
00:14:16,125 --> 00:14:17,633
okay?

206
00:14:26,004 --> 00:14:31,339
This is the house
Sun's parents used to live in together.

207
00:14:41,160 --> 00:14:45,511
But now, it's mine.

208
00:14:45,511 --> 00:14:47,519
I just bought it.

209
00:14:48,575 --> 00:14:52,328
I'm planning to use it
to teach ballroom dancing to the senior club.

210
00:15:02,711 --> 00:15:05,295
I had no idea

211
00:15:05,295 --> 00:15:08,834
that Solar went through so much as a child.

212
00:15:09,971 --> 00:15:12,518
Solar doesn't know either.

213
00:15:13,538 --> 00:15:15,539
I've never told him.

214
00:15:17,060 --> 00:15:23,736
Are you saying
Solar lost his memory when he was a child?

215
00:15:33,024 --> 00:15:35,016
The whole truth...

216
00:15:36,779 --> 00:15:38,956
is in this house.

217
00:15:44,817 --> 00:15:47,204
But can I ask you guys something?

218
00:15:47,887 --> 00:15:53,641
Please... don't tell Solar about this yet.

219
00:15:53,641 --> 00:15:56,446
There are reasons I still can't tell him.

220
00:15:57,888 --> 00:15:59,597
What reasons, Mom?

221
00:16:00,400 --> 00:16:01,894
Solar...

222
00:16:09,749 --> 00:16:10,979
Mom,

223
00:16:12,060 --> 00:16:14,837
why can't I remember
anything from my childhood?

224
00:16:15,498 --> 00:16:20,117
Why did Sun become Solar?

225
00:16:20,929 --> 00:16:22,422
Who are my real parents?

226
00:16:22,422 --> 00:16:25,315
- Solar...
- Why are you so sure

227
00:16:26,765 --> 00:16:28,943
that I'm not ready to hear the truth?

228
00:16:28,943 --> 00:16:30,419
You're not even a doctor!

229
00:16:30,419 --> 00:16:33,432
The doctor was the one who told me
not to say anything!

230
00:16:35,822 --> 00:16:37,947
When a child experiences
something traumatic...

231
00:16:37,947 --> 00:16:40,714
Your case is sensitive, Solar.

232
00:16:40,714 --> 00:16:49,032
Forgetting certain things might have been
your way of protecting yourself

233
00:16:49,032 --> 00:16:52,016
from the pain of your past.

234
00:16:52,826 --> 00:16:55,200
It'd be really dangerous

235
00:16:55,200 --> 00:16:59,020
if you found out the truth
before you were ready.

236
00:17:04,607 --> 00:17:06,810
I'm sorry...

237
00:17:09,384 --> 00:17:12,374
that I never told you anything.

238
00:17:14,454 --> 00:17:17,034
I just wasn't sure...

239
00:17:19,523 --> 00:17:21,851
I wasn't sure...

240
00:17:23,801 --> 00:17:27,523
if knowing the truth too soon...

241
00:17:30,408 --> 00:17:33,734
would make your condition worse.

242
00:17:37,901 --> 00:17:39,840
It's alright, Mom.

243
00:17:41,546 --> 00:17:44,026
I know you meant well.

244
00:17:45,329 --> 00:17:48,628
You love and worry about me.

245
00:17:52,282 --> 00:17:58,028
I just feel... a little empty somehow.

246
00:18:03,432 --> 00:18:07,939
Solar, I promise.

247
00:18:09,319 --> 00:18:11,799
When you're ready,

248
00:18:13,017 --> 00:18:16,630
I'll be the one to tell you everything.

249
00:18:17,903 --> 00:18:19,931
But for now,

250
00:18:20,949 --> 00:18:24,023
let's take it slow.

251
00:18:25,012 --> 00:18:29,831
Things are about to get better. Trust me.

252
00:19:20,492 --> 00:19:23,102
I'm sorry. That's my stomach.

253
00:19:23,102 --> 00:19:26,347
Seriously? This isn't the time to be hungry.

254
00:19:27,693 --> 00:19:32,824
Alright then, I'll make you something to eat.

255
00:19:32,824 --> 00:19:34,838
We'll leave it to you, Ma'am.

256
00:19:38,240 --> 00:19:39,245
Hey.

257
00:19:39,245 --> 00:19:41,619
They don't have to be the exact same size.

258
00:19:41,619 --> 00:19:44,498
Just chop them. We'll eat them anyway.

259
00:19:44,498 --> 00:19:45,917
Hold on.

260
00:19:45,917 --> 00:19:47,996
Why is it splashing out like this?

261
00:19:47,996 --> 00:19:49,404
It's going to splash if you do it like that.

262
00:19:49,404 --> 00:19:50,952
Here.

263
00:19:51,678 --> 00:19:54,879
Pound it hard. Really crush it.

264
00:19:54,879 --> 00:19:57,744
Keep pounding. Smash it up.

265
00:20:22,308 --> 00:20:24,148
Are you okay?

266
00:20:26,437 --> 00:20:28,246
Is there anything you want to share?

267
00:20:32,553 --> 00:20:34,338
I just feel like...

268
00:20:35,743 --> 00:20:38,334
Mom has been taking care of me all this time.

269
00:20:41,611 --> 00:20:44,122
Now she's a lot older.

270
00:20:47,836 --> 00:20:50,337
If I'm still not getting better,

271
00:20:52,449 --> 00:20:55,522
I'm scared I'll just keep
being a burden to her.

272
00:21:05,207 --> 00:21:07,113
But you still have me.

273
00:21:09,984 --> 00:21:13,736
Yeah, that's a given, isn't it?

274
00:21:16,590 --> 00:21:19,809
I wish I could help your mom cook,

275
00:21:19,809 --> 00:21:22,997
but it seems like I'm useless.

276
00:21:22,997 --> 00:21:25,036
You keep saying nonsense.

277
00:21:26,412 --> 00:21:28,252
You're right.

278
00:21:33,783 --> 00:21:39,123
Guys, this might not be the right time,

279
00:21:39,900 --> 00:21:42,342
but I really want to deal with this now.

280
00:21:43,461 --> 00:21:46,944
I don't want to wait
until I'm ready to find the truth.

281
00:21:46,944 --> 00:21:48,744
So,

282
00:21:50,807 --> 00:21:52,217
let's go to that house.

283
00:21:52,217 --> 00:21:53,679
Huh?

284
00:21:53,679 --> 00:21:57,872
Solar, is that a good idea?

285
00:21:57,872 --> 00:22:00,243
Are you sure?

286
00:22:00,966 --> 00:22:03,554
I'm not sure at all.

287
00:22:03,554 --> 00:22:07,128
But if I keep waiting,
it's just going to keep bothering me.

288
00:22:08,007 --> 00:22:12,247
I know we should take it slow,

289
00:22:13,616 --> 00:22:18,300
but I really feel like
I should know the truth now.

290
00:22:18,300 --> 00:22:23,427
But I don't think we'll get an answer
from Auntie Pranee.

291
00:22:29,246 --> 00:22:33,617
She seems to be enjoying her retirement.

292
00:22:35,496 --> 00:22:39,429
Guys, I have a plan.

293
00:22:54,772 --> 00:22:58,296
Ma'am, you're such a great cook.

294
00:22:58,296 --> 00:22:59,647
You could open a restaurant.

295
00:22:59,647 --> 00:23:03,422
Oh, you're too kind.

296
00:23:03,422 --> 00:23:07,764
I can totally vouch for that.

297
00:23:07,764 --> 00:23:10,832
Do you have any tips you can share?

298
00:23:10,832 --> 00:23:13,298
Well, I think it's my beauty.

299
00:23:13,298 --> 00:23:15,732
Oh, Ma'am.

300
00:23:15,732 --> 00:23:17,031
Right, So...

301
00:23:18,023 --> 00:23:21,243
Oh, where did Solar and Pobmek go?

302
00:23:21,243 --> 00:23:22,753
Oh, those two.

303
00:23:22,753 --> 00:23:25,238
- They just went to wash the dishes out back.
- Not again.

304
00:23:25,238 --> 00:23:27,791
Where are you going?

305
00:23:27,791 --> 00:23:29,445
You guys have no idea.

306
00:23:29,445 --> 00:23:31,332
Solar is really stubborn.

307
00:23:31,332 --> 00:23:33,015
He always insists on doing the dishes himself

308
00:23:33,015 --> 00:23:35,193
- and ends up making a mess.
- Wait, ma'am!

309
00:23:35,193 --> 00:23:36,993
Huh?

310
00:23:44,690 --> 00:23:48,428
Ma'am, I want to improve my P.E. lessons.

311
00:23:48,428 --> 00:23:50,887
I've been thinking
about teaching the kids ballroom dancing.

312
00:23:50,887 --> 00:23:54,015
Can you give me a crash course?

313
00:23:54,015 --> 00:23:55,388
Are you sure that's a good idea?

314
00:23:55,388 --> 00:23:59,430
The kids will... definitely be able to dance.

315
00:23:59,430 --> 00:24:01,603
Because I'm going to teach you all the steps.

316
00:24:01,603 --> 00:24:02,682
How do I start?

317
00:24:02,682 --> 00:24:05,277
Relax.

318
00:24:05,277 --> 00:24:06,524
Good.

319
00:24:06,524 --> 00:24:08,278
Relax.

320
00:24:32,965 --> 00:24:34,828
Where do we start?

321
00:24:38,323 --> 00:24:39,824
Hey.

322
00:25:11,480 --> 00:25:12,080
[Little Sun]

323
00:25:21,539 --> 00:25:23,719
Could these be your parents?

324
00:25:31,528 --> 00:25:35,001
[Morning with Atsara & Little Lion Solar,
8th Edition]

325
00:25:37,603 --> 00:25:39,911
Go! Step!

326
00:25:42,102 --> 00:25:44,832
And this is an ad...

327
00:25:46,505 --> 00:25:48,025
There you go.

328
00:25:48,025 --> 00:25:51,232
You're not on Premium, are you?

329
00:25:52,456 --> 00:25:53,673
Wait.

330
00:25:53,673 --> 00:25:56,564
Are Solar and Pobmek still not back?

331
00:25:56,564 --> 00:25:58,811
I'm sure they're still washing the dishes.

332
00:25:58,811 --> 00:25:59,844
They'll be back soon.

333
00:25:59,844 --> 00:26:02,133
But they're taking too long.

334
00:26:12,721 --> 00:26:15,116
You two are acting suspicious.

335
00:26:21,520 --> 00:26:24,280
[Morning with Atsara & Little Lion Solar,
8th Edition]

336
00:26:32,547 --> 00:26:37,053
♫ Let this morning catch the sun's rays ♫

337
00:26:37,053 --> 00:26:41,046
♫ Everything will fade away ♫

338
00:26:41,046 --> 00:26:47,581
♫ Happy or sad, we'll be okay ♫

339
00:26:47,581 --> 00:26:52,987
♫ The light will get us ♫

340
00:26:52,987 --> 00:26:55,120
♫ Through the day ♫

341
00:26:55,120 --> 00:26:58,640
[Atsara & Little Lion Solar]

342
00:27:00,508 --> 00:27:02,070
Is it morning already?

343
00:27:02,070 --> 00:27:04,709
Yes, it is.

344
00:27:04,709 --> 00:27:07,390
Our friends are waiting to watch us,
Little Solar.

345
00:27:07,390 --> 00:27:10,110
Then let's do some stretching.

346
00:27:10,110 --> 00:27:13,376
Let's do it together. Come on!

347
00:27:13,376 --> 00:27:15,717
Waist twists.

348
00:27:15,717 --> 00:27:17,567
Neck rolls.

349
00:27:17,567 --> 00:27:19,668
Arm circles.

350
00:27:19,668 --> 00:27:22,385
Very good!

351
00:27:22,385 --> 00:27:23,524
Look, Mom.

352
00:27:23,524 --> 00:27:26,086
I can follow along with Little Solar now!

353
00:27:26,086 --> 00:27:27,486
Waist twists.

354
00:27:27,486 --> 00:27:28,837
Neck rolls.

355
00:27:28,837 --> 00:27:30,637
Arm circles.

356
00:27:42,648 --> 00:27:44,259
Sun!

357
00:27:44,259 --> 00:27:49,220
How many times have I told you
that Little Solar is not a toy?

358
00:27:52,352 --> 00:27:54,580
Hey, stop!

359
00:27:54,580 --> 00:27:55,564
How could you do this?

360
00:27:55,564 --> 00:27:56,934
You were going to hit our child?

361
00:27:56,934 --> 00:27:58,816
Are you out of your mind?

362
00:27:59,681 --> 00:28:01,321
Stop hovering over me already!

363
00:28:01,321 --> 00:28:03,183
- Just go away!
- But who's going to take care of you?

364
00:28:03,183 --> 00:28:04,258
I don't need you!

365
00:28:04,258 --> 00:28:05,866
Go!

366
00:28:17,127 --> 00:28:18,771
Hello?

367
00:28:29,719 --> 00:28:33,130
Solar, what's wrong?

368
00:28:35,113 --> 00:28:39,821
I think I'm starting to remember
bits and pieces.

369
00:28:43,252 --> 00:28:47,382
Having you is the reason I lost everything!

370
00:28:52,710 --> 00:28:54,318
Solar.

371
00:29:08,662 --> 00:29:09,914
Mom.

372
00:29:12,086 --> 00:29:14,303
Who's my real mother?

373
00:29:16,364 --> 00:29:17,516
You're not ready.

374
00:29:17,516 --> 00:29:19,830
I'm ready, Mom.

375
00:29:19,830 --> 00:29:21,670
Just tell me.

376
00:29:25,145 --> 00:29:29,208
Mom! Just tell me!

377
00:29:29,905 --> 00:29:32,122
Who's Atsara?

378
00:29:32,784 --> 00:29:35,190
Please tell me.

379
00:29:36,215 --> 00:29:38,923
Please, Mom. Who is she?

380
00:29:38,923 --> 00:29:42,236
She's your real mother. She passed away.

381
00:29:57,351 --> 00:29:59,532
Her name was Atsara.

382
00:30:03,724 --> 00:30:06,928
She was a TV show host.

383
00:30:10,253 --> 00:30:13,319
But after she gave birth to Sun,

384
00:30:14,514 --> 00:30:17,824
her show was taken off the air.

385
00:30:18,966 --> 00:30:22,633
The station replaced it with
an animated cartoon.

386
00:30:23,742 --> 00:30:28,659
In the end,
Atsara became an artist no one would hide,

387
00:30:28,659 --> 00:30:31,114
and she fell into depression.

388
00:30:31,878 --> 00:30:34,233
She decided

389
00:30:34,960 --> 00:30:39,530
to walk out into the road with her son
to get hit by a car.

390
00:30:45,546 --> 00:30:47,307
When Sun woke up...

391
00:30:47,307 --> 00:30:49,932
Who's Sun? My name's not Sun.

392
00:30:49,932 --> 00:30:51,849
I'm Solar.

393
00:30:51,849 --> 00:30:54,140
Solar means bright sunshine,

394
00:30:54,140 --> 00:30:57,764
ready to heal everyone's heart.

395
00:31:12,886 --> 00:31:14,742
What about my father?

396
00:31:17,731 --> 00:31:21,278
Someone said your father disappeared

397
00:31:21,278 --> 00:31:23,852
after your mother passed away, Sun.

398
00:31:40,747 --> 00:31:42,747
Thank you, Mom.

399
00:31:48,404 --> 00:31:53,632
Thank you for telling me
when I could handle it.

400
00:31:56,252 --> 00:32:01,930
If you'd told me earlier,
I don't think I could've lived with it.

401
00:32:07,469 --> 00:32:09,269
Sun.

402
00:32:47,450 --> 00:32:49,292
What's on your mind?

403
00:32:54,663 --> 00:32:56,903
I'm just wondering...

404
00:32:59,429 --> 00:33:02,129
if all of this is my fault,

405
00:33:05,319 --> 00:33:10,500
if me being born... wore my mother out,

406
00:33:13,008 --> 00:33:14,833
stressed her out,

407
00:33:16,903 --> 00:33:19,344
made me such a burden that she got sick,

408
00:33:22,694 --> 00:33:25,333
and led her to make that decision.

409
00:33:30,793 --> 00:33:32,593
Solar,

410
00:33:34,089 --> 00:33:41,336
if all of this didn't happen to you,
but to me...

411
00:33:42,505 --> 00:33:45,244
what would you do?

412
00:33:51,795 --> 00:33:54,437
I'd probably pat your head,

413
00:33:55,687 --> 00:33:58,234
give you a kiss on the forehead,

414
00:33:59,773 --> 00:34:05,316
hold your hand, and tell you...

415
00:34:06,751 --> 00:34:11,028
that some things just happen.

416
00:34:13,344 --> 00:34:18,040
Good or bad, they just happen.

417
00:34:19,574 --> 00:34:21,430
I guess that's all.

418
00:34:39,148 --> 00:34:43,821
Some things just happen.

419
00:34:44,897 --> 00:34:49,424
Good or bad, they just happen.

420
00:34:50,911 --> 00:34:53,136
You copied your boyfriend's idea.

421
00:34:56,638 --> 00:34:58,761
But thank you so much.

422
00:35:22,760 --> 00:35:26,027
- Hey, is Solar asleep already?
- Yeah.

423
00:35:30,105 --> 00:35:31,639
What a shame.

424
00:35:31,639 --> 00:35:33,668
You don't see shows like this anymore.

425
00:35:33,668 --> 00:35:35,157
Times have changed.

426
00:35:35,157 --> 00:35:38,425
Kids' attention spans
are so short these days.

427
00:35:43,308 --> 00:35:45,884
Hey, what are you doing?

428
00:35:45,884 --> 00:35:48,218
I'm watching that.

429
00:35:48,218 --> 00:35:52,986
I'm just curious why the song in this show
sounds so familiar.

430
00:35:55,967 --> 00:36:00,550
♫ Let this morning catch the sun's rays ♫

431
00:36:01,196 --> 00:36:02,246
Holy shit!

432
00:36:02,246 --> 00:36:04,584
It's not shit. It's a beautiful song.

433
00:36:04,584 --> 00:36:06,280
That's not what I mean.

434
00:36:06,280 --> 00:36:10,012
This is the song that made Sun fall asleep
and wake up as Solar.

435
00:36:10,012 --> 00:36:12,604
Huh? This song?

436
00:36:12,604 --> 00:36:16,690
I thought you said it was the song
you competed with in high school.

437
00:36:16,690 --> 00:36:17,775
Yeah,

438
00:36:17,775 --> 00:36:20,737
but I must've heard this song on the show
when I was a kid

439
00:36:20,737 --> 00:36:23,383
and used the melody to write random lyrics

440
00:36:23,383 --> 00:36:25,060
and record it on the CD.

441
00:36:25,060 --> 00:36:28,139
That's why when Sun heard it, he fell asleep.

442
00:36:29,154 --> 00:36:30,925
Damn!

443
00:36:30,925 --> 00:36:32,263
What are we waiting for?

444
00:36:32,263 --> 00:36:34,256
Let's figure out the chords!

445
00:36:34,256 --> 00:36:36,083
Yeah!

446
00:36:36,083 --> 00:36:39,692
Oh, I'm so excited! What can I do?

447
00:36:39,692 --> 00:36:44,339
If you want to help, can you fix this?

448
00:36:48,001 --> 00:36:50,416
Thank you so much.

449
00:36:50,416 --> 00:36:53,701
Of course. No problem.

450
00:36:53,701 --> 00:36:55,962
Let me write the chords down.

451
00:36:55,962 --> 00:36:59,337
G.

452
00:36:59,337 --> 00:37:01,137
Minor 7.

453
00:37:01,788 --> 00:37:03,838
- Then D.
- D.

454
00:37:03,838 --> 00:37:05,339
D for duck?

455
00:37:05,339 --> 00:37:07,139
D minor.

456
00:37:09,582 --> 00:37:11,382
Hey!

457
00:37:14,092 --> 00:37:15,892
Gotcha!

458
00:37:19,052 --> 00:37:20,668
Wow.

459
00:37:20,668 --> 00:37:23,966
You're still as good as ever, huh?

460
00:37:27,784 --> 00:37:31,557
Where are the uncles and auntie?

461
00:37:31,557 --> 00:37:34,008
Why aren't they playing with us?

462
00:37:34,008 --> 00:37:38,138
Don't tell me they left me again.

463
00:37:42,105 --> 00:37:43,905
Hey.

464
00:37:45,082 --> 00:37:49,662
No one left you. Trust me.

465
00:37:54,709 --> 00:37:55,912
Yay!

466
00:37:55,912 --> 00:37:56,958
We got it, right?

467
00:37:56,958 --> 00:37:59,320
Let's see what's going on.

468
00:37:59,320 --> 00:38:01,276
We did it!

469
00:38:02,126 --> 00:38:03,790
Oh!

470
00:38:03,790 --> 00:38:05,207
Sun, sweetie!

471
00:38:05,207 --> 00:38:08,597
I fixed your doll.

472
00:38:08,597 --> 00:38:12,400
Oh! This is Little Lion Solar.

473
00:38:12,400 --> 00:38:16,336
Uncle Pobmek also has a song
he wants you to hear.

474
00:38:20,224 --> 00:38:22,750
Come on.

475
00:38:22,750 --> 00:38:23,979
Let's listen.

476
00:38:23,979 --> 00:38:25,779
Sit down.

477
00:39:54,984 --> 00:39:56,669
What are you all crowding around for?

478
00:39:57,995 --> 00:40:01,530
Are you Solar?

479
00:40:04,066 --> 00:40:05,645
Of course I am.

480
00:40:07,015 --> 00:40:10,504
Yay!

481
00:40:14,281 --> 00:40:15,903
What's going on?

482
00:40:15,903 --> 00:40:19,836
Solar, we found the song
that makes Sun fall asleep.

483
00:40:34,982 --> 00:40:36,754
Are you sure...

484
00:40:37,650 --> 00:40:39,932
you want to donate all this stuff?

485
00:40:43,595 --> 00:40:46,527
Yeah, I'm sure.

486
00:40:47,643 --> 00:40:49,611
I'll just keep these.

487
00:40:59,010 --> 00:41:01,499
That's one more thing done, right?

488
00:41:01,499 --> 00:41:05,246
You make it sound like
there's a lot to deal with.

489
00:41:05,869 --> 00:41:07,277
Exactly!

490
00:41:07,277 --> 00:41:10,935
From now on, I'll need all your help
with the school stuff again.

491
00:41:10,935 --> 00:41:14,499
The annual talent show
is coming up next week.

492
00:41:14,499 --> 00:41:18,363
Just thinking about it
makes me want to give up.

493
00:41:18,363 --> 00:41:21,874
Don't be discouraged. I'm back.

494
00:41:21,874 --> 00:41:23,589
I'll help you.

495
00:41:24,478 --> 00:41:29,580
Teacher Jee!
Come here! I'll show you more steps!

496
00:41:29,580 --> 00:41:31,526
Come on!

497
00:41:31,526 --> 00:41:33,604
We haven't told her the truth.

498
00:41:33,604 --> 00:41:34,942
We don't have to.

499
00:41:34,942 --> 00:41:38,124
You can turn this into a real lesson plan
for your students.

500
00:41:38,902 --> 00:41:40,454
Good idea.

501
00:41:40,454 --> 00:41:42,273
- Ma'am, I'm coming!
- Come!

502
00:41:42,273 --> 00:41:44,714
Give me something advanced and professional.

503
00:41:44,714 --> 00:41:47,027
Hey, Teacher Sodchuen! Join us. Come on!

504
00:41:47,027 --> 00:41:48,192
Come help him memorize the moves!

505
00:41:48,192 --> 00:41:49,966
I thought you'd never ask.

506
00:41:49,966 --> 00:41:51,328
How could I not? Come on.

507
00:41:51,328 --> 00:41:54,595
- How do we do this?
- Don't just stand there.

508
00:41:54,595 --> 00:41:56,362
Come on, guys!

509
00:41:56,362 --> 00:41:57,987
Teacher Pobmek, come on!

510
00:41:57,987 --> 00:41:59,633
Get those legs moving.

511
00:41:59,633 --> 00:42:01,358
- Move our legs.
- Yeah.

512
00:42:01,358 --> 00:42:03,508
Careful. Don't get your legs tangled.

513
00:42:26,996 --> 00:42:31,298
It feels so nice
having someone walk their fingers over me.

514
00:42:43,035 --> 00:42:44,863
This feels different.

515
00:42:45,646 --> 00:42:47,252
What are you doing?

516
00:42:48,437 --> 00:42:50,329
This isn't finger walking.

517
00:42:51,125 --> 00:42:53,039
It's me.

518
00:43:07,801 --> 00:43:10,036
Aren't you going a bit too high?

519
00:43:13,004 --> 00:43:15,004
I can go lower.

520
00:43:23,198 --> 00:43:24,638
Wait.

521
00:43:27,097 --> 00:43:28,755
Are you sure about this?

522
00:43:30,370 --> 00:43:34,612
Yeah. We're good with Sun now, right?

523
00:43:36,911 --> 00:43:38,511
That's true.

524
00:43:38,511 --> 00:43:39,828
Don't you want it?

525
00:43:39,828 --> 00:43:41,400
Of course I do.

526
00:44:03,520 --> 00:44:06,395
Good morning, boyfriend.

527
00:44:07,112 --> 00:44:11,024
The annual talent show is tomorrow!

528
00:44:11,024 --> 00:44:14,678
Teacher Pobmek, please run the stage
instead of Teacher Solar.

529
00:44:14,678 --> 00:44:16,105
Okay.

530
00:44:20,842 --> 00:44:24,216
Hey, Little Sun. You want to perform too?

531
00:44:24,216 --> 00:44:29,297
Enjoy the special performance
by Teacher Pobmek!

532
00:44:35,600 --> 00:44:37,165
Another one.

